<h1>SaveGuard Pro</h1>
<p><strong>Smart auto-save and backup plugin for Adobe Photoshop</strong></p>

<p>
SaveGuard Pro protects your work by automatically saving and backing up your Photoshop documents
based on customizable settings and intelligent activity detection. Never lose progress again.
</p>

<p><strong>Requires Photoshop 23.3.0 or later</strong></p>

<hr>

<h2>🎬 Demo</h2>
<a href="https://youtu.be/FgGDWKA0aYg">
    <img src="https://img.youtube.com/vi/FgGDWKA0aYg/maxresdefault.jpg" style="width:100%; border-radius:10px;">
</a>

<hr>

<h2>⚡ Features</h2>
<ul>
<li>AutoSave – automatic save based on detected changes</li>
<li>Smart Delay – dynamic interval adjustment</li>
<li>Cohesion Delay – waits for pause in editing</li>
<li>Interval Load Warning</li>
<li>AutoBackup – timestamped backup copies</li>
<li>Countdown timers per document</li>
<li>Save Now / Save Backup Now</li>
<li>Browse Backup Files</li>
<li>Multiple formats: PSD, PSB, PNG, JPG</li>
<li>Custom filenames and folders</li>
<li>Ignored Operations system</li>
<li>Per-document settings</li>
<li>Retry logic (up to 3 retries)</li>
<li>Crash-safe storage (.tmp / .bak)</li>
<li>Storage limits (auto cleanup)</li>
<li>11 languages support</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>📋 Requirements</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Application</th><td>Adobe Photoshop</td></tr>
<tr><th>Minimum version</th><td>23.3.0</td></tr>
<tr><th>Platform</th><td>Windows, macOS</td></tr>
</table>

<hr>

<h2>🛠 Installation</h2>
<ol>
<li>Open Adobe Photoshop</li>
<li>Go to Plugins → Browse Plugins (or Adobe Exchange)</li>
<li>Search for <strong>SaveGuard Pro</strong></li>
<li>Click Get and install</li>
<li>Open via Plugins → SaveGuard Pro</li>
</ol>

<hr>

<h2>🚀 Quick Start</h2>
<ol>
<li>Open a saved document</li>
<li>Set check interval</li>
<li>Enable AutoSave</li>
<li>Optionally enable AutoBackup</li>
</ol>

<p><strong>Note:</strong> Document must be saved at least once.</p>

<hr>

<h2>🧠 AutoSave</h2>

<h3>Primary use case</h3>
<p>
Designed for workflows where changes must propagate instantly to other tools
(e.g. 3D viewport, browser live reload).
</p>

<div class="box">
<strong>Important:</strong> Not recommended for large documents without Smart Delay.
</div>

<h3>Key Settings</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Setting</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr><td>Check interval</td><td>How often changes are checked</td></tr>
<tr><td>Smart Delay</td><td>Keeps save time ~25% of interval</td></tr>
<tr><td>Wait after edit</td><td>Delay after last action</td></tr>
<tr><td>Format</td><td>Overwrite / PSD / PSB / PNG / JPG</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Smart Delay</h3>
<p>
Automatically increases interval when saves are slow.
Never lowers below user-defined value.
</p>

<h3>Interval Load Warning</h3>
<ul>
<li>Warning ≥ 40%</li>
<li>Critical ≥ 70%</li>
</ul>

<h3>Change Detection Modes</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Direct mode:</strong> uses Photoshop saved flag</li>
<li><strong>History mode:</strong> tracks history states</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>💾 AutoBackup</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Setting</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr><td>Interval</td><td>How often backups are created</td></tr>
<tr><td>Wait after edit</td><td>Delay before backup</td></tr>
<tr><td>Format</td><td>PSD / PSB / PNG / JPG</td></tr>
<tr><td>Storage limits</td><td>Auto-delete old backups</td></tr>
</table>

<p>
Backup limits can be global (default folder) or per-document (custom folder).
</p>

<hr>

<h2>🚫 Ignored Operations</h2>
<p>
Define Photoshop history states that should not trigger saves.
Useful for actions that don't change document content.
</p>

<ul>
<li>Multiple named lists</li>
<li>Separate lists for AutoSave and AutoBackup</li>
<li>Stored as JSON</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>📁 Supported Formats</h2>

<h3>Full overwrite</h3>
<p>PSD, PSB, TIFF, PDF</p>

<h3>Single-layer only</h3>
<p>PNG, JPG</p>

<h3>Requires flattening</h3>
<p>BMP, TGA, EPS, AVIF, JXL, PCX</p>

<h3>Not supported</h3>
<p>WEBP, RAW, DDS, KTX, MPO</p>

<hr>

<h2>🔒 Privacy</h2>
<p>
All data stays local. No external transmission.
Settings stored in pluginSettings.json.
</p>

